verbs.description: frap (third-person singular simple present fraps, present participle frapping, simple past and past participle frapped)

entries.meaning: (nautical) To draw together tightly; to secure by many turns of a lashing.
examples: Next take two turns not round the spars at all but in between them round the rope itself. These turns are called "frapping" turns and must be very tight too.
Mitch and Dick took me frog frapping, too.  […]  You just shine your light in the frog's eyes, creep up on him, and frap him over the head with the stick!

Well then, what's the hottest new product line over at ubiquitous coffee retailer Starbucks — diesel fuel? No, it's not petrochemical, but neither is it coffee — rather, it's music. In Starbucks stores, you can now burn CDs while slurping a frap,  […]
